I am working on a feature for our web application that allows users to book guided tours for popular tourist destinations. I am looking for a solution to a specific issue related to the display of tour details within the booking page. When a user selects a tour, the details of that tour should be displayed at the top of the page. However, I am encountering an issue where the tour details are displayed a few pixels below the top of the page. I am using the following code to display the tour details:

```javascript
var selectedTour = getSelectedTour();
var tourDetails = document.getElementById('tour-details');
tourDetails.innerHTML = getTourDetails(selectedTour);
tourDetails.scrollIntoView(true);
```

The tour details are displayed correctly but a few pixels below the top of the page. How can I ensure that the tour details are displayed at the exact top of the page?
